We recommended that Management:

Adopt the use of Requisition and Issuance Slip (RIS) in each issuance of supplies and consolidate the RIS into Summary of Supplies and Materials Issued (SSMI) and furnish the Municipal Accountant the same to facilitate the timely and accurate presentation of the inventories on hand in the Financial Statements;
Require the Inventory Committee to conduct physical inventory taking of all the assets of LGU-Jose Panganiban, both PPEs and Supplies Inventory Annually;
Submit the properly accomplished Reports of Physical Count of Inventories (RPCI) as prescribed by existing regulations to the accounting department and the Commission on Audit (COA);
Maintain SLC per stock number; and

Reconcile the Inventory Accounts per books with the actual supplies inventory at hand.

We recommended that the LCE:
Direct the concerned offices to hasten the implementation of the partially and unimplemented PPAs under 20 per cent DF to fully attain the desired socio-economic development and environmental management outcomes essential to the promotion of the general welfare of its constituents;
Adopt a well-defined strategy to enhance the present monitoring and review activities during the planning, procurement, contract implementation and program evaluation phase, in order for the planners and implementers to continuously monitor the timely implementation, so that immediate appropriate and corrective actions could be done on noted gaps along the way;
Determine the total unobligated balances of completed PPAs and cause the reversion to unappropriated surplus for reprogramming in CY 2022; and
Make an assessment of all PPAs not yet implemented in the current year and prior years continuing to determine whether the funding for such PPAs are necessary, if not then revert to the unappropriated surplus and reprogram to development projects of utmost concern of the Municipality.

We recommended that the Management take the following courses of actions:

Direct the Municipal Accountant with the help of related officer concerned to review and recheck the validity and correctness of claims Receivables. If proven uncollectible initiate a request for write-off from the COA pursuant to COA Circular No. 2016-005 in order to present the current assets reliable in the financial statements;
Require the Municipal Treasurer to strengthen the collection process and monitoring of the receivables of the Municipality to avoid future loss due to write off of uncollectible accounts.

We recommended that the Management take the following courses of action:

Prioritize and fast-track the preparation of MCLUP before the end of the three-year period of the elected officials;
With collaboration with the Sangguniang Bayan, immediately enact the MCLUP;
Make certain that Comprehensive Development Plan (CDP) and Executive and Legislative Agenda align with the completed MCLUP; and
Ensure to update the MCLUP when necessary.

