We recommended that Management take the following courses of action:

Ensure to conduct an initial reasonable assessment on the feasibility of the location of the proposed projects to be funded by various NGAs under its different programs, by tapping various relevant units within the LGU to avoid delays and uncertainty on the projects’ implementation;

Follow strictly the project implementation schedule of the Construction of Evacuation Center at Sitio Ulipanan, Barangay Dahican to avoid further delays;



Follow-up the status of the Letter to the DILG and take as other appropriate actions necessary to warrant positive results;




If practicable, ensure prompt implementation of projects, maintain a database of information regarding, but not limited to, geo-hazard areas within the Municipality and the areas covering the ancestral domain of the Indigenous People, in relation to the usual requirements of national government funded projects of the Environmental Compliance Certificate (ECC), Certification that the project location was outside the geo-hazard zones, and National Commission on Indigenous People (NCIP) Certificate of Non-Coverage (CNC); and

When practicable, utilize electronically available and reliable information from different NGAs, such as, but not limited to, the Mines and Geosciences Bureau’s (MGB) Geo-Hazard Maps viewable and downloadable online at the MGB’s webpage.

We recommended that Management take the following courses of actions:

a. Ensure that during the identification of the projects proposed to be funded by different NGAs, the LGU is secured that the relevant requirements including, but not limited to, ECC and CNC, will be complied with to warrant its timely implementation once these projects are approved and funds are received by the LGU for such purpose;

b. Follow strictly the project implementation schedule of the Construction of Water System at Barangay Tamisan to avoid further delays;

c. Guarantee compliance with the required documents by the NCIP Regional Office No. V to warrant its eventual issuance of the certification exempting the project from submitting CNC after ensuring preventive and mitigating measures are in placed to avoid any form of harm to the inhabitant Indigenous People or any form of destruction in the Indigenous People ancestral domain; and

d. If practicable, ensure prompt implementation of projects, maintain a database of information regarding, but not limited to, geo-hazard areas within the Municipality and the areas covering the ancestral domain of the Indigenous People, in relation to the usual requirements of national government funded projects of the ECC, Certification that the project location was outside the geo-hazard zones, and CNC.

